# Plan — TeleHealthy Voice Ops Console

## Demo Concept (locked)
Single-screen web app: "TeleHealthy Voice Ops Console." Four tabs: Inbound, Outbound, CRM, Analytics. Hero tab open on load. Simulates an AI-powered healthcare voice platform — labeled as simulation. AI conversation is genuinely client-side (WebGPU via WebLLM) with deterministic scripted fallback.

## Prototype vs Full
FULL. No cap trips. Hero (WebGPU in-browser LLM conversation) is client-side — no backend needed. All CRM/telephony/SMS simulated with mock data. Frontend-only self-contained app. No Flask blueprint needed (session-only transcript store is sufficient for the demo).

## Tech Stack
- **Build:** Vite + React 18, base `/demos/telehealthy/`, output to `../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/telehealthy/`
- **AI engine:** `@mlc-ai/web-llm` (CDN ESM), model `Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct-q4f32_1-MLC` (researcher to confirm exact ID + CDN import)
- **Scripted fallback:** rule-based intent detection + response tree when WebGPU unavailable or user skips model load
- **Fonts:** Inter (UI) + DM Mono (transcript bubbles) from Google Fonts
- **No backend**

